cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.RO 

This paper proposes a generative model for object-oriented representation learning in sequential data, specifically in video data. The paper focuses on scalability, which is a common concern in computer vision and machine learning research. The proposed model uses attention and proposal-rejection mechanisms to handle a large number of objects, making it relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The model is also unsupervised, which is a common theme in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. The use of background modeling and handling of complex scenes may also make it relevant to robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with sequential data, which may make it relevant to neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
